If a man bequeath a thing belonging to him, and afterwards aliene it, most jurists agree that the bequest is not only avoided at civil law, but recovers no validity by the senatusconsult, because, even when a thing is bequeathed by condemna· tion and afterwards aliened, al· though the contention of a right by the suing legatee is valid, it is geue- rally agreed that his claim is coun- terpoised by the plea of fraud, as contravening the testator's intention.
